OL,7,FThe world's biggest trial of a four-day
OL,8,Fworking week has been hailed a "major
OL,9,Fbreakthrough" after nearly every
OL,10,Fcompany involved said they will keep to
OL,11,Fthe shorter week following the pilot.
OL,13,FSome 61 firms signed up to the trial,
OL,14,Fwhich started in June 2022 and ran for
OL,15,Fsix months. Crucially, the firms had to
OL,16,Fmake sure there was no reduction in
OL,17,Fwages for their employees.
OL,3,CTrials of four-day working week led to
OL,4,Cless stress, better health and higher
OL,5,Cprofits
